Data + editing

data321 = read.spss("HBSC 2014 5 countries.sav", to.data.frame=TRUE)

data321$drink33 <- ifelse(data321$alcltm == "Never", 0, 1)
data321$aggress33 <- ifelse(data321$beenbullied == "Haven't", 0, 1)

findata <- data321[c("drink33", "aggress33", "m96", "friendhelp", "friendshare", "friendtalk", "sex", "AGE")]
findata$friendhelp <- as.numeric(findata$friendhelp)
findata$friendshare <- as.numeric(findata$friendshare)
findata$friendtalk <- as.numeric(findata$friendtalk)
findata$AGE <- round(findata$AGE)
findata <- na.omit(findata)

Part1

Descriptive statistics

Creating function for defining mode

function.mode <- function(x) {
  theonly <- na.omit(unique(x))
  theonly[which.max(tabulate(match(x, theonly,  nomatch = NA_integer_, incomparables = NULL)))]
}

Model (drinking logit)

mod77 <- glm(as.factor(drink33) ~ friendhelp + friendtalk + m96 + sex + AGE,
             family = binomial(link = logit), findata)

summary(mod77)

First of all, it is important to mention that all variables are significant.

Each extra point of friendhelp variable decrease logarithm of odds ratio of drinking by -0.05.

Each increase of friendtalk variable increase logarithm of odds ratio of drinking by 0.05.

If person meets with friends less than weekly, it increase logarithm of odds ratio of drinking by 0.54.

If person meets with friends weekly, it leads to growth of logarithm of odds ratio of drinking by 0.98.

If person meets with friends Daily, it rise the logarithm of odds ratio of drinking by 0.97.

For girls, the logarithm of odds ratio of drinking decreases by -0.31.

Each extra point of age increase logarithm of odds ratio of drinking by 0.51.

exp(coef(mod77))
##                          (Intercept)                           friendhelp 
##                          0.000474694                          0.953564187 
##                           friendtalk                  m96Less than weekly 
##                          1.053848107                          1.719665237 
##                            m96Weekly m96Daily (specified in own variable) 
##                          2.672528779                          2.685994044 
##                              sexGirl                                  AGE 
##                          0.737015777                          1.669622788

Each extra point of friendhelp variable decrease odds ratio of drinking by almost 5%

Each increase of friendtalk variable increase odds ratio of drinking by 5%.

If person meets with friends less than weekly, it increase odds ratio of drinking by 72%.

If person meets with friends weekly, it leads to growth of odds ratio of drinking by 165%.

If person meets with friends Daily, it rise the odds ratio of drinking by 163%.

For girls, odds ratio of drinking decreases by 26%.

Each extra point of age increase odds ratio of drinking by 67%.

Model fit.

library(DescTools)
PseudoR2(mod77)
##  McFadden 
## 0.1617599

Pseudo r (mcfadden) is high (0.161>0.1). So model fits data well.

library(pscl)
hitmiss(mod77)
## Classification Threshold = 0.5 
##         y=0  y=1
## yhat=0 9268 3363
## yhat=1 3121 6158
## Percent Correctly Predicted = 70.41%
## Percent Correctly Predicted = 74.81%, for y = 0
## Percent Correctly Predicted = 64.68%  for y = 1
## Null Model Correctly Predicts 56.54%
## [1] 70.40621 74.80830 64.67808

Null model predicts = 57% of data.

Model correctly predicts 70% of data, that is quite good.

It predicts better absence of alcohol consumption than drinking.

Model (bulling probit)

mod99 <- glm(as.factor(aggress33) ~ friendhelp + friendshare + m96 + sex + AGE,
             family = binomial(link = probit), findata)

summary(mod99)

Only variables: friendhelp, friendshare, m96Less than weekly, m96Weekly and AGE are significant.

Each extra point of friendhelp variable decrease logarithm of odds ratio of bulling by -0.09.

Each increase of friendshare variable decline logarithm of odds ratio of bulling by -0.03.

If person meets with friends less than weekly, it decrease logarithm of odds ratio of bulling by -0.04.

If person meets with friends weekly, it decline logarithm of odds ratio of bulling by -0.07.

Each extra point of age decrease logarithm of odds ratio of bulling by -0.05.

exp(coef(mod99))
##                          (Intercept)                           friendhelp 
##                            2.0169108                            0.9133239 
##                          friendshare                  m96Less than weekly 
##                            0.9750128                            0.9585674 
##                            m96Weekly m96Daily (specified in own variable) 
##                            0.9294377                            0.9579166 
##                              sexGirl                                  AGE 
##                            0.9798179                            0.9547716

Each extra point of friendhelp variable decrease odds ratio of bulling by ~9%.

Each increase of friendshare variable decline odds ratio of bulling by ~3%.

If person meets with friends less than weekly, it decrease odds ratio of bulling by ~4%.

If person meets with friends weekly, it decline odds ratio of bulling by ~7%.

Each extra point of age decrease odds ratio of bulling by ~5%.

Model fit.

## 0.02098335

Pseudo r (mcfadden) is Low (0.02<0.1). So model fits data badly.
